 von Fontanes kritischem Schreiben werden im Vergleich mit den Äußerungen von Kunstfachleuten wie Waagen, Kugler, Eggers und Pietsch herausgearbeitet. Darüber hinaus erweist sich die kunstkritische Tätigkeit Fontanes auch als Laboratorium seiner Ausbildung genuin narrativer Verfahren.  aThis monograph is the first comprehensive appraisal of Theodor Fontane's complete works of art criticism in all its relevant contexts. It situates Fontane's writings on art between the realms of the Berlin School's fully differentiated academic art scholarship and that of feuilleton art criticism, and includes references to his personal writings and fictional works.  afunded by SNF  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aGerman literature. 4aFontane, Theodor. 4aKunstkritik. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aTheodor Fontane, art criticism.2 aSNFefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831105161280 cprintz978311051466740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110516098zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110516098zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110516098.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3 DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DKUb2017  aZDB-23-GOA